17/07/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- On Tuesday (15 July), the European Commission approved the annual programme for Albania, under which 46.5m euros will be extended.The funds are earmarked for encouraging economic development, fighting crime, refurbishing the court system and improving the training of clerks.
Meanwhile, the IMF authorised Albania to draw $6m.
The approval followed the Fund's second review of the economy.
(Albanian Daily News - 16/07/03)
